title: Socceroo Sainsbury to join Inter Milan | Football | Sporting News
text:
January 31, 2017 10:24am EST January 31, 2017 7:45am EST Socceroos defender Trent Sainsbury is reportedly set to join Italian Serie A heavyweights Inter Milan. Sporting News 
Published on Jan. 31, 2017 
Jan. 31, 2017 
Socceroos defender Trent Sainsbury will join Italian Serie A heavyweights Inter Milan on loan from Chinese Super League club Jiangsu Suning until the end of the season. 
MORE: WATCH: Ryan Griffiths tells Wanderers fans not to write him off | 
As initiially reported by Sky Sports , Sainsbury will join Inter as a replacement for Andrea Ranocchia, who is heading to the English Premier League on a loan deal to Hull City. 
The recent changes to CSL rules reducing the number of foreign players permitted in the match-day squad from four to three, also played a role in Sainsbury's departure. 
Inter Milan and Jiangsu Suning are owned by the same company. 
The 25-year-old Australian joined Jiangsu Suning at the start of the current campaign after two years with Dutch club PEC Zwolle. 
He has scored two goals in 29 appearances in the CSL.
